Clare Nessling, director at Conti, a UK-based mortgage broker which arranges loans for Britons buying in Europe, agreed: "Spain has had its problems but its core appeal hasn't changed. For many it's a lifestyle choice – they're attracted by the climate and culture rather than by earning a prospective fortune. You can still buy with confidence."
